[{"id":16811,"date":"2025-07-22T17:58:51","modified":"2025-07-22T18:04:50","slug":"introducing-atlasbase-your-new-star-atlas-companion","link":"https:\/\/aephia.com\/star-atlas\/introducing-atlasbase-your-new-star-atlas-companion\/","title":{"rendered":"Introducing AtlasBase \u2013 Your New Star Atlas Companion"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">If you\u2019ve been around online games for a while, you may remember the Blizzard forums, in which case, you\u2019ve probably used Blizzard\u2019s legendary <strong>Blue Tracker<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">It is a simple feed that pulled together every developer post across countless threads. Whenever a Blizzard dev dropped a nugget of insight\u2014or a cryptic teaser\u2014it would light up in blue, standing out sharply against the sea of white community messages. And thanks to the Blue Tracker, you didn\u2019t need to scour the forums to find it. It just <em>showed up<\/em>, neatly collected on a dedicated page.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">That iconic blue might\u2019ve started with Blizzard (though no one ever officially confirmed it), but it didn\u2019t end there. Over the years, many games and communities (such as <strong>Star Citizen<\/strong> and <strong>Star Atlas<\/strong>) have followed suit, using blue to highlight developer or team posts. And Blue Trackers? They became a staple for dedicated fans, cutting through the noise to deliver the signal. These days, almost every major studio uses some version of a Blue Tracker.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">But there has been one glaring omission \u2026 until now.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"576\" src=\"https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AtlasBase-Flyer-1024x576.jpeg\" alt=\"AtlasBase Flyer\" class=\"wp-image-16812\" srcset=\"https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AtlasBase-Flyer-1024x576.jpeg 1024w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AtlasBase-Flyer-300x169.jpeg 300w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AtlasBase-Flyer-768x432.jpeg 768w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AtlasBase-Flyer-1536x864.jpeg 1536w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AtlasBase-Flyer-1320x743.jpeg 1320w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/AtlasBase-Flyer.jpeg 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Proudly presenting: AtlasBase!<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">We\u2019re excited to unveil <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/atlasbase.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>AtlasBase<\/strong><\/a><\/strong>, a Star Atlas hub built <em>by<\/em> the community, <em>for<\/em> the community, and a new initiative by <strong>Aephia Industries<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">At launch, AtlasBase features two (we hope) helpful tools:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\ud83d\udfe6 Blue Tracker<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Our take on the classic Blue Tracker, tailored for Star Atlas and its primary gathering place: <strong>Discord<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">We track and surface messages from official team members across all key public channels. The feed is filterable, searchable, and saves you from endlessly scrolling to find a passing comment that might have been posted at 3 a.m. your time. Sure, Discord\u2019s search works\u2014but only if you already <em>know<\/em> what you\u2019re looking for.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"856\" data-src=\"https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.45.59-1024x856.png\" alt=\"AtlasBase - Team Tracker\" class=\"wp-image-16818 lazyload\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.45.59-1024x856.png 1024w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.45.59-300x251.png 300w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.45.59-768x642.png 768w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.45.59.png 1189w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 1024px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 1024\/856;\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">AtlasBase &#8211; Team Tracker<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">A Blue Tracker flips that around. It provides you with full awareness of everything being said by the team. No fear of missing out, no wondering what flew under the radar, you just check in and stay effortlessly up to date.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">This only recently became possible thanks to <strong>Darwiin<\/strong>, ATMTA\u2019s support superhero and a rising star in the vibe-coder scene, who built a Discord bot that exports team messages via API. Thanks to his work, we can now present official communications in a clear, centralized, and easy-to-follow manner.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">\ud83c\udf0d Meetup Dashboard (with 3D Map)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><em>Star Atlas is more than a game; it\u2019s a global community.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Over the past few years, we\u2019ve seen only a handful of real-life meetups, with roughly half of them organized by <strong>Funcracker<\/strong> around the <strong>Solana Breakpoint<\/strong> conferences. But 2025 seems to mark a turning point!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">With the DAO\u2019s Ecosystem Fund opening up, and recent initiatives like the <strong>Community Meetup Fund<\/strong> (<em><a href=\"https:\/\/govern.staratlas.com\/proposals\/f15380c9-8d3f-4849-8185-c29f4c72e961\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Iris Bounty: The Feast<\/a><\/em>) being approved, we\u2019re now seeing more organized gatherings, not necessarily taking place alongside events where the team has a presence.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">With this new wave of energy, it was high time to bring some structure and visibility to what\u2019s happening across the world.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"557\" height=\"1024\" data-src=\"https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.29.27-557x1024.png\" alt=\"AtlasBase - Meetup Dashboard\" class=\"wp-image-16816 lazyload\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.29.27-557x1024.png 557w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.29.27-163x300.png 163w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.29.27-768x1411.png 768w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.29.27-836x1536.png 836w, https:\/\/aephia.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/07\/Screenshot-2025-07-22-at-19.29.27.png 879w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 557px) 100vw, 557px\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 557px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 557\/1024;\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">AtlasBase &#8211; Meetup Dashboard<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Enter the <strong>Meetup Dashboard<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">At the top of the page, you\u2019ll find a <strong>3D Earth<\/strong> with pins marking upcoming meetup locations, a fun, interactive way to visualize the community\u2019s global footprint. But the real utility lies just below: a <strong>chronological list<\/strong> of all upcoming events, complete with dates, locations, and links. Whether you\u2019re organizing, attending, or just curious, it\u2019s now easier than ever to stay in the loop.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">\ud83d\udc49 Want your meetup featured? Just <strong>DM Funcracker<\/strong> (DMs are open) and we\u2019ll get it added.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Why AtlasBase?<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">AtlasBase is just getting started.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">Our vision is to grow it into a <strong>mainstay utility hub<\/strong> for the entire Star Atlas community, a living base of operations packed with valuable tools, data, and insights.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">The Blue Tracker and Meetup Dashboard are just the opening salvo. <em>There\u2019s much more to come.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">So go check it out. Bookmark it. Share it. And let us know what <em>you<\/em> want to see next.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\"><a href=\"https:\/\/atlasbase.io\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><strong>Welcome to AtlasBase<\/strong>!<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"wp-block-paragraph\">\u2014The Aephia Team<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>We\u2019re excited to introduce AtlasBase, a new Star Atlas hub built by Aephia Industries\u2014for the community, by the community.<\/p>\n<p>At launch, AtlasBase features two core tools: a Discord Blue Tracker that surfaces team messages across public channels, and a Meetup Dashboard that lists upcoming real-life events, complete with a 3D globe and chronological event view.<\/p>\n<p>Track the signal. Join the journey.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2}]